100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 17, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva to discuss ongoing tensions in the Ruhr Valley, as Germany faced economic instability and political unrest. Meanwhile, in the United States, Prohibition remained a contentious issue, with ongoing debates over its effectiveness and the rise of bootlegging operations. In London, the government announced plans for a new housing initiative aimed at addressing the post-war housing crisis affecting many citizens.
